3. Architecture & Adaptive Control

3.1 Lifted Hierarchical Core

· High‑level module f_H: Enforced contractive via spectral normalisation and regularisation (k_H \approx 0.5). Maintains abstract plan z^H.
· Low‑level module f_L: Near‑unitary (allowed k_L \approx 0.99) to perform expressive, non‑linear refinement.
· Memory m_t = \mathcal{M}(z_t, m_{t-1}): GRU with spectral normalisation; part of the joint monotone operator.

3.2 Adaptive Halting with Energy Monitor

We combine ACT‑style halting with the Lyapunov energy:

h_t = \sigma(W_h s_t + b_h), \quad p_{\text{halt}}^{(t)} = h_t \prod_{\tau=0}^{t-1} (1 - h_\tau).

Inference terminates when p_{\text{halt}}^{(T)} > \tau_{\text{halt}} or \mathcal{E}(s_T) < \epsilon_{\mathcal{E}}. Ponder cost \mathcal{L}_{\text{halt}} = \lambda_{\text{ponder}} \sum_t p_{\text{halt}}^{(t)}.

3.3 Verifier/Critic Integration

A lightweight constraint checker v_\phi(s, x) outputs logical consistency scores. Auxiliary loss \mathcal{L}_{\text{critic}} = \|v_\phi(s^*, x) - 1\|^2.

---

4. Training Objective

\mathcal{L} = \underbrace{\mathcal{L}_{\text{task}}(s^*, y)}_{\text{Task}} + \lambda_1 \underbrace{\mathcal{E}(s^*)}_{\text{Residual}} + \lambda_2 \underbrace{\mathcal{L}_{\text{halt}}}_{\text{Compute}} + \lambda_3 \underbrace{\mathcal{L}_{\text{mono}}}_{\text{Monotonicity}} + \lambda_4 \underbrace{\mathcal{L}_{\text{critic}}}_{\text{Consistency}}.

Gradients flow through s^* via implicit differentiation with exact VJP.

