6. Applications to Embodied Systems

The monotone operator formulation yields exponential stability with a flexible rate:

\|\delta s(t)\| \leq e^{-\mu t} \|\delta s(0)\|,

where \mu is the monotonicity constant. The adaptive step size \gamma_t allows the system to initially respond quickly to large errors (high energy) and then settle precisely. This is ideal for real‑time robotics and BCIs, where both reactivity and stability are required.

